/* ============================================================================
 *  Patchgram native overlay (AppKit / Objective-C; the dylib is compiled with
 *  -x objective-c -framework AppKit). Gated by g_overlay_enabled.
 *  A floating circular "open" button (the same info.circle glyph as the patcher's
 *  About button) toggles a half-transparent settings panel that carries a close (X)
 *  in its top-right corner (closes the panel, the open button stays), an "Animation"
 *  row with a macOS NSSwitch, and a "Select png" row with an NSOpenPanel picker.
 *  All three are NSPanel CHILD windows of the Telegram main window, so they track it
 *  and never steal key focus. The chosen .png + the Animation flag persist to
 *  ~/Library/Application Support/Patchgram/overlay_state.plist and drive the
 *  stage-2 profile "rain" animation. Everything is logged via patchgram_log.
